Come on. I sold them all
in like a week.

28:57.111 --> 28:59.011
Don't mess around, neighbour.

29:55.708 --> 29:57.583
Please don't do this to us
again.

29:59.917 --> 30:02.000
Remember what happened last
time.

30:02.042 --> 30:03.667
With your last project.

30:04.333 --> 30:05.958
You ended up at a grocery store.

30:07.792 --> 30:09.917
Then in the psych ward.

30:11.875 --> 30:13.792
Forget about last time.

30:15.417 --> 30:17.333
This time I have Ben.

31:38.672 --> 31:40.472
Was there
drinking involved?

31:40.474 --> 31:42.607
Of course not!

31:44.078 --> 31:46.244
Why would you even
ask me that?

31:46.246 --> 31:48.547
I just wanted to make sure.

31:48.549 --> 31:51.249
You know that drinking
eliminates the effects

31:51.251 --> 31:53.018
of the medication.

31:53.020 --> 31:55.387
Your moods can start
shifting again.

31:55.389 --> 31:58.056
Everyone's mood shifts.

31:58.058 --> 32:01.093
I believe it's called...

32:01.095 --> 32:03.362
- human nature?
- Of course.

32:04.531 --> 32:07.065
But changes can be a little bit
more severe

32:07.067 --> 32:09.067
after everything that
you've gone through.

32:09.069 --> 32:13.005
The war, the unstable economic
situation,

32:13.007 --> 32:14.639
being a young mother...

32:14.641 --> 32:17.376
Nina...

32:17.378 --> 32:19.644
is the best thing I've
ever done in my life!

32:19.646 --> 32:21.513
Yes, of course.

32:23.150 --> 32:25.217
It's just that it was around
then

32:25.219 --> 32:27.686
that you started to experience
the mood swings,

32:27.688 --> 32:29.621
the instability...

32:29.623 --> 32:32.124
and finally,
you were diagnosed.

32:34.028 --> 32:35.627
I knew you would think that.

32:37.431 --> 32:40.599
Uh, I'm gonna be going. Uh...

32:42.169 --> 32:44.636
I could be doing better things.

32:46.173 --> 32:49.141
And what would you like to be
doing right now instead?

32:49.143 --> 32:52.644
I told you. I have a lot
of work to do on Easy Land

32:52.646 --> 32:55.280
before I hand it to Ben.

32:55.282 --> 32:58.550
Oh. I didn't know Benjamin
had given you a deadline.

32:58.552 --> 33:00.318
He didn't.

33:00.320 --> 33:02.521
I gave myself a deadline.

33:04.358 --> 33:08.260
Um, actually I-I have some
bills to pay

33:08.262 --> 33:11.797
and this project
is gonna help with that.

33:11.799 --> 33:13.565
I hope.

33:18.272 --> 33:20.105
Listen Doc um...

33:22.309 --> 33:25.077
I know you don't believe in me

33:26.146 --> 33:28.280
and that's quite all right.

33:28.282 --> 33:30.248
I really mean it.

33:33.253 --> 33:35.587
But please explain me one thing:

33:37.224 --> 33:39.758
why is it so wrong

33:39.760 --> 33:42.127
to feel things?

33:42.129 --> 33:44.162
To have emotions?

33:44.164 --> 33:46.364
What-what's wrong with that?

33:50.571 --> 33:53.271
I see that you are a highly
intelligent

33:53.273 --> 33:55.173
and talented woman, Jasna.

33:56.276 --> 33:58.410
And there's a part of your
disease

33:58.412 --> 34:00.779
that makes you feel that
you can achieve anything.

34:02.850 --> 34:07.152
You may feel really great,
sharp,

34:07.154 --> 34:10.188
ten times more productive
than usual...

34:12.126 --> 34:14.192
until you don't anymore.

34:14.194 --> 34:16.261
And then it gets ugly,

34:16.263 --> 34:19.898
it gets really ugly
really fast, doesn't it?

34:19.900 --> 34:22.601
- Hm?
- Mhmm.

34:24.438 --> 34:26.771
And that's why the medication
is so important.

34:30.811 --> 34:33.278
- I understand.
- Do you?

34:33.280 --> 34:34.579
I do.

34:35.849 --> 34:37.716
I really do.

34:40.487 --> 34:44.322
So now you can go
to government people

34:44.324 --> 34:47.759
and tell them that
I've been doing great.

34:47.761 --> 34:49.728
I am very proactive

34:49.730 --> 34:52.731
and contributing
to the community.

34:56.403 --> 34:57.636
- Jasna,
- Hmm?

34:58.839 --> 35:00.772
have you been taking
the medication

35:00.774 --> 35:02.641
that I prescribed for you?

35:03.677 --> 35:05.844
Of course.

35:07.314 --> 35:08.914
What?

35:08.916 --> 35:10.649
You don't believe me?

35:10.651 --> 35:12.851
Oh, it's not that
I don't believe you.

35:12.853 --> 35:14.920
It's just that I'm afraid that
if it goes untreated...

35:14.922 --> 35:16.688
Thank you, Doctor.

35:18.725 --> 35:21.326
- I-I appreciate that?
- Do you?

35:22.429 --> 35:24.296
Oh I do.

35:25.899 --> 35:28.733
- I'm trying... so hard.
- Mhmm.

35:29.937 --> 35:32.404
I'm...

35:32.406 --> 35:34.439
I'm doing my best.

35:40.247 --> 35:42.280
Are you with me, girls?

35:43.550 --> 35:46.518
Am I right, girls?

35:46.520 --> 35:47.919
Are you with me?

35:47.921 --> 35:49.988
Oh my God.

35:52.326 --> 35:55.393
Am I right, girls?
Am I right?

35:58.865 --> 36:00.599
<i>You're late.</i>

36:00.601 --> 36:02.767
Come on in.

36:02.769 --> 36:04.636
Take a seat beside me now.

36:10.677 --> 36:12.644
You two.

36:12.646 --> 36:14.479
You're in the same sinking ship.

36:14.481 --> 36:16.248
Take a look at the wall.

36:17.284 --> 36:18.650
What do you see?

36:18.652 --> 36:20.552
I see an exercise
for grade one students.

36:22.356 --> 36:23.755
Seriously, come on,

36:23.757 --> 36:25.590
this assignment is a waste
of time.

36:25.592 --> 36:28.058
Psychology has proven

36:28.060 --> 36:30.527
that sometimes we may need a
way to visualize our goals,

36:30.530 --> 36:32.998
otherwise they might seem
incomprehensible.

36:34.668 --> 36:36.801
<i>You two have one more week,</i>

36:36.803 --> 36:38.737
<i>brainstorm together.</i>

36:41.642 --> 36:43.308
All right. Well, sure.

36:43.310 --> 36:45.410
if the school pysch has proven
it works

36:45.412 --> 36:47.279
then, I wanna play
for La Liga,

36:47.281 --> 36:48.747
grow a new knee cap
that's not injured,

36:48.749 --> 36:51.983
and travel back in time.
Can I go now?

36:54.488 --> 36:57.389
Visualizing a real goal might
have helped your brother.

36:58.825 --> 37:01.026
<i>Please think about it.</i>

37:06.533 --> 37:08.466
Do you know how old he is?

37:10.037 --> 37:11.903
Like 19?

37:11.905 --> 37:14.339
Almost 21.

37:14.341 --> 37:16.441
Next year he'll be going
to adult school

37:16.443 --> 37:18.443
if he wants to finish grade 12.

37:18.445 --> 37:20.345
Do you wanna go to adult school?

37:20.347 --> 37:22.747
No, I'm going to Serbia.

37:22.749 --> 37:25.583
Then, perhaps you'll take
this last chance

37:25.585 --> 37:27.585
a little more seriously

37:27.587 --> 37:29.654
and actually help Greg.

38:57.477 --> 38:59.077
<i>When will she be
back, do you know?</i>

38:59.079 --> 39:01.179
<i>I don't know,
I just got home.</i>

39:01.181 --> 39:03.415
- Maybe she's at work.
- You must tell her,

39:03.417 --> 39:05.116
is no joke this time!
This time she very, very late.

39:05.118 --> 39:07.485
And she not pay gas bill
since in January.

39:07.487 --> 39:09.087
How do you think I feel?

39:09.089 --> 39:11.423
- Pretty bad.
- I'm finding new tenants.

39:11.425 --> 39:13.625
Wait.

39:18.031 --> 39:20.165
How is this to start?

39:20.167 --> 39:21.966
Give it back to her.

39:21.968 --> 39:24.702
Sunraj, give it back to her!

39:27.073 --> 39:31.209
You'll get everything by the
end of the week, as I promised.

39:31.211 --> 39:33.211
What's wrong with you, Sunraj,

39:33.213 --> 39:35.046
taking money from my child?

39:35.048 --> 39:37.682
Jasna, you must understand
debt is debt.

39:37.684 --> 39:39.884
You owe over $3,000.

39:39.886 --> 39:42.220
We had eviction hearing
last week,

39:42.222 --> 39:44.122
you didn't come, why?

39:44.124 --> 39:45.690
You know what that means?

39:45.692 --> 39:47.659
I have full right
to kick you out.

39:47.661 --> 39:50.094
Mr. Chopra, how long have
we known each other?

39:50.096 --> 39:52.564
Almost two years!

39:52.566 --> 39:54.833
I know I've been late
a few times,

39:54.835 --> 39:57.735
but have I ever not paid you?

39:57.737 --> 40:00.672
Mrs. Djuric,
I give you chance,

40:01.875 --> 40:04.209
one last chance -

40:04.211 --> 40:07.512
you pay by the end of the week
or I have no choice.

40:07.514 --> 40:09.547
- I call the police. Hm?
- I'll see you on Friday.

40:09.549 --> 40:11.182
Yes.

40:41.014 --> 40:42.947
<i>How much do we owe?</i>

40:42.949 --> 40:45.216
Don't worry about it.

40:45.792 --> 40:47.000
Go do your homework.

40:47.042 --> 40:48.708
Don't worry about it. I'm going
to take care of everything.

40:48.750 --> 40:50.542
- We were supposed to go
to Serbia this summer.

40:51.875 --> 40:54.042
But you fucked everything up.

40:54.083 --> 40:56.125
I didn't get to see my friends.

40:57.208 --> 40:59.958
I'll go back to Serbia myself
and stay at grandma's.

41:01.083 --> 41:03.167
Nina what's going on with you?

41:03.750 --> 41:05.333
You never tell me anything
anymore.

41:06.125 --> 41:08.208
Who hit you?

41:10.083 --> 41:13.458
It's their fault you hate it
here so much.

41:13.875 --> 41:15.958
Who did this to you?

41:17.500 --> 41:18.375
It's okay.

41:19.250 --> 41:21.458
Some girl Shandra, but I hit her
back.

41:22.667 --> 41:24.167
I wasn't a victim.

41:24.750 --> 41:26.625
Everything will be okay.

41:27.375 --> 41:29.375
All will be good.

41:32.833 --> 41:35.292
And you know what we'll do?

41:36.875 --> 41:40.583
We will create 'Nina's section'.

41:41.167 --> 41:42.792
You want to?

41:42.833 --> 41:44.500
That's what we'll do.

41:44.750 --> 41:45.417
Look...

41:46.250 --> 41:48.958
We'll put a part here for you.

41:49.792 --> 41:54.208
You just have to tell me what
you want and something you like.

42:02.042 --> 42:04.125
Yes, I'll let you know.

43:43.830 --> 43:46.230
Hi guys, you know
where Shandra is?

43:46.232 --> 43:48.266
- Right over there.
- Oh thanks.

43:52.806 --> 43:55.306
I know. It's just hard...
like I can't be here.

43:55.308 --> 43:58.209
Hey girls. Can you give us
a moment please.

43:58.211 --> 43:59.944
Thanks.

43:59.946 --> 44:01.979
- You Shandra?
- Yeah.

44:04.317 --> 44:06.417
You the one going around
hurting other people?

44:06.419 --> 44:07.952
Fuck off, lady.

44:07.954 --> 44:09.287
- Oh what was that?
- What the fuck?

44:09.289 --> 44:11.189
- Let me go.
- Oh sure I will.

44:11.191 --> 44:13.057
But first we're gonna have
a serious conversation

44:13.059 --> 44:14.759
about your behaviour.

44:14.761 --> 44:16.461
Okay. You're legit crazy!

44:16.463 --> 44:19.263
Oh, is that so?
Well, how about you, huh?

44:19.265 --> 44:21.933
Going around and hurting
other people?

44:21.935 --> 44:24.102
- Is that okay? Huh?
- No.

44:24.104 --> 44:25.870
- Hm? What?
- No.

44:25.872 --> 44:27.872
What was that?
What did you say?

44:27.874 --> 44:29.140
No, no, it's not.
It's not okay.

44:29.142 --> 44:31.943
It's not okay. Good.

44:35.081 --> 44:36.848
Don't make me come again.

44:42.922 --> 44:45.490
Oh, Mrs. Fraser.
Hi, how are you?

44:45.492 --> 44:48.059
- Great. How are you?
- Good. I'm Nina's mom.

44:48.061 --> 44:50.027
Nina's really progressing
at the theatre.

44:50.029 --> 44:51.896
You should be very happy.

44:51.898 --> 44:54.365
Oh. Good to know.
Thank you.

44:54.367 --> 44:56.234
- Bye bye.
- Hope everything's well.

44:56.236 --> 44:58.035
Bye.

45:05.311 --> 45:07.145
<i>Could you pass the salt?</i>

45:11.084 --> 45:12.483
Thank you.

45:19.025 --> 45:21.259
Hey, you want some
dessert?

45:22.495 --> 45:24.462
No, that's okay.

45:24.464 --> 45:27.331
But I baked this cake
just for you!

45:29.102 --> 45:31.102
Here...

45:31.104 --> 45:32.870
try some.

45:37.343 --> 45:41.279
Oh, come on, it's not that bad,
is it?

45:42.549 --> 45:45.216
- Jesse?
- Ah!

45:45.218 --> 45:47.418
You jerk.

45:47.420 --> 45:50.288
Here. Some milk.

45:50.290 --> 45:52.023
Oh, you got that right
into my eyes!

45:52.025 --> 45:53.925
What are you doing?!
What are you doing?!

45:53.927 --> 45:55.927
Oh yeah.

45:55.929 --> 45:58.396
- Lenny is burnt.
- Stanley!

45:58.398 --> 46:00.965
Oh, no-no-no.

46:00.967 --> 46:03.901
Oh! It's mustard time!
Mustard time.

46:03.903 --> 46:06.103
Mustard time.

46:10.443 --> 46:12.310
- No, no, no, no, no.
- It's for you.

46:12.312 --> 46:14.111
Here. Oh no!

46:16.249 --> 46:17.615
You really got me.
You really got me

46:17.617 --> 46:19.016
Guys, you really got me.

46:19.018 --> 46:20.551
Oh, you really got me
on the chest, guys.

46:24.324 --> 46:26.290
Ahhh!

46:28.161 --> 46:30.294
- Ouch!
- That was good.

46:30.296 --> 46:33.164
Well, I never.

46:39.472 --> 46:41.339
<i>You know we're counting
on ticket sales, man,</i>

46:43.943 --> 46:46.210
<i>Oh man, we could really use
your help on tech week.</i>

46:48.047 --> 46:50.214
<i>Yeah, yeah,
we do have someone else,</i>

46:50.216 --> 46:52.516
but she's just-she's just a kid,
it's...

46:54.187 --> 46:56.621
it is no the same.

46:56.623 --> 47:00.124
<i>Okay, sure, bye.</i>

47:05.198 --> 47:07.632
Oh. Can I have a smoke?

47:17.143 --> 47:19.543
So why "Endgame"?

47:21.314 --> 47:23.915
It's a very important piece
for an audience to experience.

47:23.917 --> 47:26.050
Experience what?
Nothing happens.

47:27.954 --> 47:29.687
Why does anything
have to happen?

47:32.358 --> 47:34.926
Because...

47:34.928 --> 47:37.962
because a story is suppose
to have some kind of plot,

47:39.432 --> 47:43.134
and then some kind of
resolution... I don't know,

47:44.437 --> 47:46.170
basically something happens
that gives people hope,

47:46.172 --> 47:47.705
and not just tells them
we live for nothing.

47:47.707 --> 47:49.040
Beckett sucks.

47:53.446 --> 47:55.446
It may help you to know that uh,

47:57.016 --> 47:58.516
Beckett thinks that there is
nothing more funny

47:58.518 --> 48:00.418
than unhappiness.

48:04.324 --> 48:06.324
Yeah, of course he does.

48:26.245 --> 48:27.478
Okay, we're back!

48:27.480 --> 48:29.213
Call the actors.

48:29.215 --> 48:30.681
Let's go.
Let's get started.

48:40.560 --> 48:42.126
Okay.

48:42.128 --> 48:44.695
Jasna, uh...

48:44.697 --> 48:47.665
if you don't have any prior
arrangements tonight,

48:47.667 --> 48:50.468
could you possible stay
a little later today

48:50.470 --> 48:53.337
- and just clean up a bit.
- Of course.

48:53.339 --> 48:56.040
Only if I'm not
inconveniencing you.

48:56.042 --> 48:58.242
I've just that I've been
noticing a lot of dust around.

48:58.244 --> 49:00.444
And I don't have time to
maintain the washroom so.

49:00.446 --> 49:02.513
Oh no worries, I'll take care
of everything.

49:02.515 --> 49:04.415
Great. Thank you.

49:04.417 --> 49:06.717
Linda, I'm so sorry,
do you have a minute?

49:06.719 --> 49:08.552
Well, um... I gotta get
to the doctors office so.

49:08.554 --> 49:10.688
Oh, I-I hate to ask, but um,

49:10.690 --> 49:13.090
can I get a little advance now?

49:13.092 --> 49:15.459
It will help me greatly with
some bills that I have to pay.

49:15.461 --> 49:17.161
Well, I'm in a rush right now.

49:17.163 --> 49:19.030
So we'll talk about it later,
okay?

49:19.032 --> 49:21.766
Sure. Okay.
Can I remind you this Friday?

49:21.768 --> 49:23.768
- About this.
- Sure. Friday is good.

49:23.770 --> 49:26.070
Good, great.

49:29.609 --> 49:31.709
Th-thanks.

50:24.764 --> 50:27.465
- Just say it.
- Say what?

50:27.467 --> 50:29.700
My mom's crazy.

50:29.702 --> 50:31.368
Naw, your mom's lit.

50:31.370 --> 50:33.204
Shandra had it coming.

50:36.275 --> 50:38.876
Hey look, I know a place
where we can go hang out.

51:24.290 --> 51:26.524
Come on, Arman. Are you
actually cool with failing?

51:28.561 --> 51:30.528
Since when do you care
so much anyway?

51:30.530 --> 51:32.496
I thought you had
your escape plan.

51:46.179 --> 51:47.778
What you got there?

51:47.780 --> 51:49.680
Mrs. Fraser has chained me
to a theatre.

51:49.682 --> 51:51.615
How is that goin' for you?

51:51.617 --> 51:53.450
It's okay.

51:53.452 --> 51:56.620
If you like watching grown
adults play like children.

51:56.622 --> 51:58.722
Dealing with this arrogant
director

51:58.724 --> 52:01.258
who thinks he knows everything.

52:01.260 --> 52:03.360
There is nothing more
funny than unhappiness.

52:04.764 --> 52:06.830
Shit, that sounds horrible.

52:09.936 --> 52:11.535
Your turn.

52:24.650 --> 52:26.417
You wanna be a mechanic
like your dad?

52:28.387 --> 52:31.989
You think you're the only one
planning on ditchin' this wasteland.

52:31.991 --> 52:34.558
I'd be down just takin' the car
and bookin' it too, you know?

52:34.560 --> 52:36.594
Booking it where?

52:36.596 --> 52:38.762
My bro's got this really great
gig up north.

52:40.299 --> 52:41.899
I mean, who cares if he
didn't finish high school?

52:43.302 --> 52:44.702
It pays a shit ton!

52:46.505 --> 52:48.405
How do you think
we really getting by?

52:49.609 --> 52:51.775
By sellin' stolen phones?

52:53.012 --> 52:54.678
Hell no, I'm done
with that shit.

52:56.349 --> 52:57.715
So when is the trip?

52:58.918 --> 53:01.719
I dunno. It depends.

53:17.036 --> 53:19.870
You want me to go up there?

53:19.872 --> 53:22.640
With the polar bears
and the oil rigs?

53:22.642 --> 53:24.608
Yo, it's just a drawing.

53:24.610 --> 53:26.844
Mrs. Fray,
told us to visualize.

53:36.322 --> 53:37.755
Sorry.

53:39.025 --> 53:41.492
- For what?
- It's complicated.

53:42.728 --> 53:45.362
Just chill out will you?

54:07.353 --> 54:10.788
Not bad. You can also do
the windows.

54:10.790 --> 54:13.657
Mark the windows because the
lighting is coming in later

54:13.659 --> 54:15.559
and we can give them
some reference.

54:15.561 --> 54:17.061
Anything else?

54:17.063 --> 54:19.096
Yes, you will be also be
doing props.

54:19.098 --> 54:22.766
<i>Stanley is gonna show you
The inventory backstage.</i>

54:22.768 --> 54:25.669
- Aren't you, Stanley?
- Oh yeah, of course, why?

54:25.671 --> 54:27.938
<i>Okay.</i>

54:31.444 --> 54:32.943
Where is my pie?

54:34.714 --> 54:36.814
Wow, nice tape job, shadow.

54:38.117 --> 54:41.018
Or should I say, our new SM?

54:42.121 --> 54:44.388
Um, what's SM?

54:47.093 --> 54:48.692
Props are back here.

54:51.597 --> 54:53.564
See, Larry is the Stage Manager,

54:53.566 --> 54:55.065
but he barley shows up.

54:55.067 --> 54:56.800
And God know Greg is lost
with out him.

54:56.802 --> 54:59.403
So that's why it's really
awesome that you're here.

54:59.405 --> 55:01.672
- Greg doesn't like me.
- Yes he does.

55:01.674 --> 55:03.674
He thinks you have an
interesting point of view.

55:03.676 --> 55:05.743
- I told him Beckett sucks.
- Yeah. Exactly.

55:05.745 --> 55:07.611
This, I thinks it's broken.

55:07.613 --> 55:09.580
So you'll have to try
to find a way to fix that.

